Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior glazed, with two added red bands lined in white; exterior: dotted rosette with three bands below; narrow stripe at top of lip; inscription cut on lower body, on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.843)
